Lactalis 'sticks milk' to its wrist with Andalusian farmers: it loses 130 million liters by refusing to sell it to them and they become part of Covap .- The pulse that began 
Lactalis
 Puleva against some Andalusian farmers over the price of milk has already been resolved. The members of the Alba Ganaderos cooperative, at a meeting held on May 9, decided to almost unanimously support the position and management that the cooperative, through its governing council, and has chosen not to sign 
The contract imposed by this dairy company that involved a reduction of 9 cents
 in the price paid for a liter of milk, an obligation to deliver 100% of the volume of milk, and a duration of one year, although they decided to commit to the evaluation of an index to revise prices starting in August of this year.

400,000 liters of milk a day in the sewer until a price agreement is reached .- Milk producers from provinces such as Seville, Malaga and Granada have begun to throw the milk to draw attention to the drop in the price of the product that, in their opinion, Grupo Lactalis is trying to impose “paying nine cents less per liter”, actions that have already represented the loss of about 400,000 liters per day since last Monday, which they expect to continue until there is an agreement with the French multinational.

This has been explained to Europa Press by sources consulted at COAG, which this Tuesday holds an internal meeting in Seville in which provincial representatives of the agrarian and livestock organization will discuss joint protest actions.

Farmers in Andalusia throw away milk from their farms because they do not reach an agreement with Lactalis .- Farmers throw milk away

Milk farms in Andalusia are throwing away their production 
as a measure of protest and denounce
 after not reaching an agreement with the company Lactalis Puleva for the sale of the product.
According to COAG, the French multinational company, in the midst of a crisis due to inflation, 
Impose a reduction of 9 cents per liter of milk 
which means unaffordable losses of about 20,000 euros per month per month on average per production, a reduction that makes dozens of farms unfeasible. There are almost two hundred affected farmers throughout Andalusia, all of whom have refused to sign the contract for the time being.

Dairy sheep are facing the decisive part of the year with a fall of 9.8% in the first quarter .- Official statistical data from the Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food (MAPA)
The sheep's milk market is in an unusual situation. With exceptionally high prices, which in the case of Castilla-La Mancha are already at levels that are difficult to imagine even for the most optimistic of farmers, production continues to decline. The reason is the rise in food costs.
The data for the month of March from the 'Report on statements of the first buyers of sheep and goats', prepared by the General Subdirectorate of Livestock and Hunting Productions of the 
Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food (MAPA)
, based on statements from the dairy industries, indicates that the sheep's milk market is in decline in production.

Farmers estimate that they will throw away 400,000 liters of milk a day because of the low prices .- Milk producers in provinces such as Seville, Malaga and Granada have begun to throw away the milk to draw attention to the drop in the price of the product that, in their opinion, Grupo Lactalis is trying to impose 'paying nine cents less per liter', actions that have already represented the loss of about 400,000 liters per day since last Monday, which they expect to last until there is an agreement with the French multinational. This has been explained to Europa Press by sources consulted at COAG, which this Tuesday holds an internal meeting in Seville in which provincial representatives of the agrarian and livestock organization will discuss joint protest actions.

The rise in milk prices does not stop the decline in production .- Falling milk production, a significant increase in prices that barely compensates for the increase in production costs on farms and a certain moderation in the abandonment of production by the livestock subsector are the ingredients of the cow's milk market at the beginning of 2023, reflecting a marked change of direction in the sector.
Official statistics from the beginning of this year indicate that cow's milk production continues to fall, especially in the most peripheral regions, despite the strong increase in prices recorded throughout the country.

Barbón (PSE) is committed to creating an autonomous Asturian song award .- OVIEDO, 30 (EUROPA PRESS)
 The president of the Asturian Government and candidate for re-election by the Socialist Party, Adrián Barbón, has committed himself this Sunday to creating an autonomous award for Asturian songs in the next legislature. This was stated by the socialist leader after attending the final of the Asturian Song Competition 'Conceyu de Siero', which was held this morning at the Teatro Auditorio de Pola de Siero. The socialist explained that his commitment comes after the proposal of the Friends of Tradition Folklore Association (Afatra).
